  h2 Details

  p.
    Compare the new logo with the previous version, which was in use for the
    past decade. It featured the as-of-then corporate typeface with a narrow
    band of the four primary Microsoft colors. 

  figure
    a(href='logo/msrd-old-96px.jpg')
      img(src='logo/msrd-old-96px.jpg', width=212, height=96)
    figcaption rd logo prior to 2013

  :markdown
      Then contrast the new logo within the larger Microsoft [product family like Office and Xbox](http://www.neowin.net/news/the-new-microsoft-brand-family-at-a-glance).

  p More details about the logo files
    ul
      li Rendered from Adobe Illustrator 
      li File size minimized and optimized with <a href='http://optipng.sourceforge.net'>OptiPNG</a>
      li Image height is evenly divisble by 16 or 24 pixels for typographical baseline
      li The logo is a 3 Â½ : 1 ratio  
      li The screen color is <span class="invert">rgb (0, 125, 195)</span> or
         <span class="invert">hsl (202, 100%, 38%)</span>
      li For print, use <span class="invert">cmyk (85, 50, 0, 0)</span>
      li.
         Designed by Sean Dolinsky at <a href="http://www.vertigo.com">Vertigo</a>. 
         Some of his <a href='logo/sketches.png'>early sketches</a>.

  :markdown
    Explore the source code at [github](http://github.com/msrd/msrd.io).

